cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to solve a semantic text question similarity task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also utilizes pre-trained embeddings and neural networks, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The task involves predicting the relation between question pairs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of self-attention in the model suggests the possibility of it belonging to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
